<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-09-09T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-09-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5045/191: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-09T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 9,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>238. Your 354, August 27, 9 a.m. Associate Justice E. Finley Johnson of
                            the Supreme Court of the Philippine Islands will be named as the
                            American judge to serve on Commission of Inquiry at Shanghai as soon as
                            Department receives word from you as to when the Commission will
                            sit.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>